{{More footnotes|date=December 2014}} {{Infobox album | name = Julekonserten | type = Live album | artist = | cover = Julekonserten.jpg | alt = | released = 1995 | recorded = | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Christmas music|Christmas]], [[Folk music|Folk]], [[Traditional]] | length = | label = | producer = | prev_title = | prev_year = | next_title = | next_year = }} {{Infobox album | name = Julekonserten 10 år | type = Live album | artist = | cover = Julekonserten_10_år.jpg | alt = | released = 1999 | recorded = | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Christmas music|Christmas]], [[Folk music|Folk]], [[Traditional]] | length = | label = | producer = | prev_title = | prev_year = | next_title = | next_year = }}
'''Julekonserten''' was a Norwegian Christmas concert which was held every year between 1989 and 1999. ''Julekonserten'' toured in [[Scandinavia]], and visited cities in [[Norway]], [[Sweden]] and [[Denmark]] with a mix of Scandinavian artists. The long list of artists and performers includes [[Sissel Kyrkjebø]], [[The Chieftains]], [[Oslo Gospel Choir]], [[Triple & Touch]], [[Rune Larsen]], [[Tor Endresen]] and Kurt Ravn. Every year ''Julekonserten'' (the concerts in [[Oslo]] and [[Gjøvik]]) was also broadcast on Television in Norway, Sweden and Denmark. Stageway AS arranged these concerts and a part of the money went to aid children on the street in La Paz and Santa Cruz in Bolivia.
Two CDs were released from their concerts, ''Julekonserten'' (1996) and ''Julekonserten 10 år'' (1999).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sissel.net/cds.html|title=CDs|work=Sissel.net|accessdate=5 December 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209151350/http://www.sissel.net/cds.html|archivedate=9 December 2014|df=}}</ref> A rare recording of [[Sissel Kyrkjebø]] performing [[My Tribute (To God Be The Glory)]] with [[Oslo Gospel Choir]] at Julekonserten 1997 in [[Gjøvik]] can be found on the 1998 compilation album ''The Best of Sissel''.
